WEBVTT

00:00.294 --> 00:02.140
(Arion) No Elf has ever
traveled beyond the Breakline.

00:02.219 --> 00:05.170
- Without an army, you won't survive.
- Which is why I need a guide.

00:05.172 --> 00:06.755
- Slanter.
- (growling)

00:06.807 --> 00:08.006
Proposition.

00:08.007 --> 00:10.842
- Your help in exchange for your freedom.
- You must be desperate.

00:10.844 --> 00:12.344
Dagda Mor has returned.

00:12.396 --> 00:14.479
The quest is more important
than any one life!

00:14.515 --> 00:16.347
You can't let your
emotions get in the way!

00:16.400 --> 00:20.268
(Eventine) The Ellcrys seed must be
carried to a place called Safehold.

00:20.320 --> 00:23.238
She's not gonna help us if we keep
her dragged along like a prisoner.

00:23.273 --> 00:25.740
Are you sure you don't want her
hands free for some other reason?

00:25.776 --> 00:27.192
(roaring)

00:27.244 --> 00:28.527
Fire those stones up, kid!

00:28.579 --> 00:30.195
They're not working. Time for plan "B."

00:31.498 --> 00:32.948
(roaring)

00:33.000 --> 00:34.166
(laughing)

00:34.201 --> 00:35.634
I told you I had a plan.

00:35.669 --> 00:38.537
- I deserve the crown.
- No one deserves the crown.

00:40.082 --> 00:41.423
Then I'll just have to take it.

00:44.287 --> 00:46.086
Long live the king.

00:49.299 --> 00:51.249
♪♪

00:53.000 --> 00:59.074
Learn the unknown words of this movie
--->   Skeebdo.com

01:02.012 --> 01:02.928
(gasping slightly)

01:05.933 --> 01:06.982
Shh.

01:07.017 --> 01:08.099
Come on.

01:08.101 --> 01:09.601
Where are you taking me?

01:09.603 --> 01:11.102
It's a surprise.

01:11.155 --> 01:13.939
I've had enough surprises
for one lifetime.

01:24.952 --> 01:26.284
Wil!

01:37.297 --> 01:39.598
Wil?!

01:39.633 --> 01:41.216
Damn you.

01:41.268 --> 01:42.133
(gasping)

01:48.559 --> 01:50.642
It still works.

01:53.113 --> 01:55.146
(squeaking)

01:55.199 --> 01:56.982
Climb on.

01:57.034 --> 02:01.987
♪ She sold her heart forever ♪

02:01.989 --> 02:04.990
♪ And now she's rusting out ♪

02:05.042 --> 02:09.461
♪ She waits here in the garden ♪

02:09.496 --> 02:10.662
See?

02:10.663 --> 02:12.330
It's fun, right?

02:13.634 --> 02:16.334
(laughing)

02:18.088 --> 02:21.139
I do have feelings for you.

02:21.174 --> 02:24.509
And you thought you'd show
me by sleeping with Eretria?

02:24.561 --> 02:26.111
(laughing)

02:26.146 --> 02:28.179
Only because I couldn't
have what I really wanted.

02:29.516 --> 02:34.853
♪ It's so unreal ♪

02:37.190 --> 02:39.441
♪ It's... ♪

02:39.493 --> 02:42.027
(laughing)

02:45.332 --> 02:50.952
♪ It's so unreal ♪

02:53.373 --> 02:57.959
♪ It's always... ♪♪

02:58.011 --> 02:59.878
Amberle...

03:01.214 --> 03:04.049
(laughing maniacally)

03:04.051 --> 03:05.884
♪♪

03:05.886 --> 03:10.221
♪ I feel it runnin' through my veins ♪

03:35.716 --> 03:40.418
♪ I need that fire just to know ♪

03:40.420 --> 03:42.921
♪ That I'm awake ♪♪

03:43.029 --> 03:44.998
- sync and corrections by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

03:45.125 --> 03:47.258
It's okay, you're awake.

03:47.311 --> 03:48.259
What happened?

03:50.230 --> 03:52.263
You were moaning in your sleep, Princess.

03:52.316 --> 03:54.766
Dreaming about the Mongrel's
pouty lips, no doubt.

03:54.818 --> 03:56.768
(chuckling wryly)

03:59.156 --> 04:00.942
We need to go, this place isn't safe.

04:01.274 --> 04:01.614
Why?

04:02.326 --> 04:03.161
What did you see?

04:03.610 --> 04:05.527
There's a storm coming.

04:05.579 --> 04:06.427
A big one.

04:06.613 --> 04:07.614
We need to move.

04:07.917 --> 04:08.505
Let's go.

04:14.037 --> 04:16.870
♪♪

04:22.095 --> 04:24.429
(footsteps approaching)

04:24.464 --> 04:25.200
Where's your brother?

04:25.882 --> 04:27.841
Hopefully halfway to Tyrsis by now.

04:28.552 --> 04:30.208
He's gone to petition the Federation.

04:30.520 --> 04:33.138
He believes that building a
coalition with the Humans

04:33.190 --> 04:35.223
is key to surviving the Demon siege.

04:35.275 --> 04:38.143
Your brother is a fool, but no matter.

04:38.145 --> 04:40.224
We have more pressing concerns.

04:42.949 --> 04:45.150
(door opening)

04:47.621 --> 04:49.487
The Druid has been lying to us.

04:57.381 --> 04:58.013
Is this...

04:58.582 --> 05:00.415
The Blade of the Warlock Lord.

05:00.467 --> 05:03.968
Forged by the Druid order
to overcome dark magic.

05:04.004 --> 05:07.839
Strong enough to defeat the Dagda Mor.

05:07.841 --> 05:09.224
I thought this was destroyed after

05:09.259 --> 05:10.975
- the Second War of the Races.
- So did I.

05:11.011 --> 05:16.765
But according to the Codex, it lies
concealed in a vault beneath our city.

05:16.817 --> 05:18.683
Now the Druid must have known that.

05:18.735 --> 05:20.101
Why would he hide such a thing?

05:20.153 --> 05:21.519
You said he could be trusted,

05:21.521 --> 05:23.938
you said that he was the only
one with the power to protect...

05:23.990 --> 05:28.526
I know what I said and
I know what I've done.

05:28.578 --> 05:29.994
(sighing)

05:30.030 --> 05:33.948
But if my fears are right,
then we are vulnerable.

05:34.000 --> 05:35.200
I should have trusted you.

05:38.981 --> 05:40.512
I'll find this blade.

05:41.174 --> 05:43.505
And if the Druid proves to be our enemy,

05:44.211 --> 05:46.224
then we will face him together.

05:48.048 --> 05:49.521
Thank you, son.

05:50.767 --> 05:52.380
You're the only one I can trust.

05:58.558 --> 06:00.942
(wind whistling)

06:00.977 --> 06:02.727
(Crispin) We need to find Safehold.

06:02.779 --> 06:04.395
We'll rest when we've
reach the Mermiddon.

06:07.284 --> 06:09.200
Am I the only one who
thinks staying the course

06:09.236 --> 06:10.401
is a bad idea?

06:10.454 --> 06:13.037
- What do you mean?
- That Demon at the fort?

06:13.073 --> 06:14.456
It knew we were coming.

06:14.491 --> 06:15.957
That's impossible.

06:15.992 --> 06:18.543
Allanon said the Dagda Mor
had a spy at Arborlon.

06:18.578 --> 06:20.700
The Changeling. We saw it die.

06:21.748 --> 06:23.955
- There could be another.
- He's right.

06:25.051 --> 06:26.417
We need to find another
way to the Wilderun.

06:26.419 --> 06:27.752
(Crispin) There is no other way.

06:27.804 --> 06:29.471
Those mountains are impassable.

06:29.506 --> 06:30.421
There's always Pykon.

06:32.092 --> 06:34.008
It offers passage through the Rock Spur

06:34.060 --> 06:35.760
and into the Wilderun beyond.

06:36.255 --> 06:36.958
Pykon?

06:37.230 --> 06:38.897
A fairy tale, Princess.

06:38.932 --> 06:40.317
Pykon's no fairy tale.

06:40.734 --> 06:42.066
My parents died in the dungeons

06:42.102 --> 06:43.601
of that stinking Elvin fortress.

06:45.272 --> 06:46.988
While we argue, that storm is closing in.

06:47.023 --> 06:48.273
If you want to spend the next six days

06:48.325 --> 06:51.409
walking around the damn
mountain, be my guest!

06:51.444 --> 06:52.552
I'm outta here.

06:53.530 --> 06:54.380
Wait.

06:55.448 --> 06:56.325
Take us there.

06:57.667 --> 07:00.451
- How long will it take?
- Half a day's climb, tops.

07:00.504 --> 07:03.621
Try anything, and I'll let
Crispin finish what he started.

07:09.296 --> 07:10.630
(Crispin) Scouts, move out.

07:11.131 --> 07:12.458
And keep your eyes open.

07:13.433 --> 07:15.633
(wind whistling)

07:18.188 --> 07:21.773
♪♪

07:23.810 --> 07:26.644
(growling)

07:32.810 --> 07:34.342
♪♪

07:48.373 --> 07:49.802
You shouldn't be here.

07:50.333 --> 07:51.146
I just...

07:51.919 --> 07:52.982
wanted to see him.

07:53.653 --> 07:55.428
He cannot sense your presence.

07:55.874 --> 07:56.956
Or your affection.

07:56.981 --> 07:58.481
Then do something.

07:58.517 --> 07:59.483
You let this happen!

07:59.517 --> 08:00.850
Heal him or...

08:00.852 --> 08:03.986
I'm trying, but his mind has gone dark.

08:05.907 --> 08:07.940
♪♪

08:07.992 --> 08:10.192
(screaming)

08:11.743 --> 08:13.915
_

08:13.998 --> 08:16.532
(Bandon) Get me out of here!

08:16.584 --> 08:18.367
- Help me!
- _

08:18.422 --> 08:20.422
_

08:20.505 --> 08:22.371
(screaming)

08:23.875 --> 08:25.708
Resist him, boy!

08:28.946 --> 08:31.212
_

08:31.696 --> 08:32.969
_

08:34.018 --> 08:36.719
(screaming)

08:41.525 --> 08:43.058
(screaming)

08:46.731 --> 08:47.947
Let her go!

08:49.233 --> 08:50.199
(groaning)

08:54.739 --> 08:56.028
Explain yourself.

08:56.574 --> 08:57.740
Go now.

08:59.744 --> 09:01.293
Leave me!

09:16.761 --> 09:19.929
The king believes that the
Druid may have been corrupted

09:19.931 --> 09:22.181
by the very same demon
leading the attacks.

09:22.233 --> 09:24.066
If that's true, then Allanon
may have sent Amberle

09:24.101 --> 09:25.818
into a trap.

09:25.853 --> 09:28.103
Cat, I need your help.

09:28.156 --> 09:32.158
There is a weapon hidden in
a vault below the palace.

09:32.193 --> 09:34.610
If the Druid really is lost,
it might be our only chance

09:34.662 --> 09:36.245
to defeat the Dagda Mor.

09:36.280 --> 09:37.947
I would do anything to avenge the Chosen,

09:37.999 --> 09:39.198
but I don't know of any weapon.

09:39.250 --> 09:40.449
But you know this palace.

09:40.501 --> 09:42.585
There are miles of tunnels below.

09:42.620 --> 09:45.171
It's got to be somewhere that
no one would think to look.

09:49.861 --> 09:52.245
I've heard whispers about a
chamber beneath the dungeons.

09:53.297 --> 09:56.215
Some of the servants say it's
cursed, but it's just talk.

09:56.267 --> 09:57.633
Show me.

10:00.438 --> 10:02.188
♪♪

10:05.726 --> 10:07.276
(horse neighing)

10:16.037 --> 10:17.703
Slanter, wait.

10:27.999 --> 10:29.882
(Slanter) No...

10:29.917 --> 10:30.692
No.

10:31.836 --> 10:33.168
My people!

10:33.221 --> 10:35.471
Slaughtered by Demons.

10:35.506 --> 10:37.473
These monsters don't discriminate.

10:37.508 --> 10:39.675
If we don't unite against them,
more innocents will die.

10:42.096 --> 10:46.849
I must say last rites, to
release their spirits.

10:46.901 --> 10:48.434
It is our custom.

10:48.486 --> 10:49.685
(Tilton) We're almost at the Breakline.

10:49.687 --> 10:51.353
We don't have time.

10:55.326 --> 10:57.243
(lock unlatching)

11:01.699 --> 11:03.249
We'll make time.

11:05.202 --> 11:07.369
What are you doing?

11:07.371 --> 11:09.371
We've been at war with
the Gnomes for 30 years.

11:09.423 --> 11:10.923
Now we have a common enemy.

11:10.958 --> 11:12.841
This is an opportunity.

11:15.046 --> 11:17.463
Your earthly body yields.

11:17.515 --> 11:23.302
Flesh transformed to clay and
ash to fertilize the fields.

11:23.354 --> 11:27.056
Born anew, conveyed on wings of light,

11:27.108 --> 11:31.610
to go with our fallen kin
beyond the skies of sight.

11:35.935 --> 11:36.755
We should go.

11:38.736 --> 11:39.785
(growling)

11:41.872 --> 11:43.205
Don't do this.

11:43.240 --> 11:44.872
Get back.

11:51.632 --> 11:53.465
(horses neighing)

12:02.593 --> 12:04.560
(growling)

12:07.732 --> 12:10.099
(roaring)

12:10.101 --> 12:11.483
(wind whistling)

12:12.770 --> 12:14.570
(grunting)

12:33.874 --> 12:34.356
Here!

12:48.022 --> 12:50.272
It should be here!

12:50.307 --> 12:52.141
Maybe it's the next peak over!

12:52.193 --> 12:53.642
Maybe it doesn't exist at all!

12:53.644 --> 12:55.644
Your stupidity is going
to get us all killed!

12:55.646 --> 12:57.946
(Cephalo) Well, I heard zero
good ideas from you, Captain!

12:57.982 --> 13:00.149
(Crispin) Here's an
idea... I slit your throat

13:00.201 --> 13:01.900
and use your body to fuel our fire.

13:01.952 --> 13:04.486
Killing each other won't
get us off this mountain!

13:06.741 --> 13:08.624
Guys?

13:31.098 --> 13:33.599
Nice-looking fairy tale, isn't it?

13:33.651 --> 13:34.683
(chuckling)

13:43.778 --> 13:48.414
♪♪

13:52.253 --> 13:53.368
(Amberle) Come on.

13:54.705 --> 13:55.921
(door creaking)

13:55.956 --> 13:57.873
(wind whistling)

14:10.438 --> 14:11.937
(lock latching)

14:20.281 --> 14:23.232
Home sweet home.

14:23.234 --> 14:25.484
(Wil) Looks abandoned.

14:25.536 --> 14:27.453
Looks can be deceiving.

14:36.547 --> 14:39.381
♪♪

14:44.016 --> 14:45.232
(Crispin) Who the hell is she?

14:58.162 --> 15:00.612
Anyone else have a
problem with this plan?

15:00.614 --> 15:03.865
Following a creepy kid through
an abandoned fortress?

15:03.918 --> 15:05.450
Not at all.

15:18.716 --> 15:20.565
Welcome.

15:20.601 --> 15:22.017
Please forgive my appearance,

15:22.052 --> 15:24.770
it's been a long time
since we had any company.

15:24.805 --> 15:26.138
You were expecting us?

15:26.190 --> 15:29.107
Mag saw you coming up the mountain.

15:29.143 --> 15:31.443
Where are my manners?

15:31.478 --> 15:32.978
I am Dontes Remikin.

15:32.980 --> 15:35.480
My friends call me Remo.

15:35.532 --> 15:36.898
What friends?

15:36.951 --> 15:39.318
Well, back when we were operational.

15:39.320 --> 15:41.486
These days it's just Mag and me.

15:44.041 --> 15:46.124
Sir, Crispin Edensong,

15:46.160 --> 15:47.993
Captain of the Home Guard of Arborlon.

15:48.045 --> 15:49.161
You commanded this fort?

15:49.213 --> 15:51.580
I was an officer during the war.

15:51.632 --> 15:54.216
Now I'm just a... a caretaker.

15:54.251 --> 15:55.334
We heard this place might offer

15:55.386 --> 15:57.336
passage beyond the mountains.

15:57.388 --> 16:00.672
There is nothing beyond the
mountains but the Wilderun.

16:00.724 --> 16:02.924
That is no place for Elves.

16:02.977 --> 16:04.393
We're on an urgent mission

16:04.428 --> 16:06.678
on the orders of King Eventine Elessedil.

16:09.266 --> 16:11.933
Then it is an honor to
host such esteemed guests.

16:11.986 --> 16:14.019
I'm afraid the passage you seek

16:14.021 --> 16:16.154
was destroyed two winters ago.

16:16.190 --> 16:18.857
It collapsed in an avalanche.

16:18.859 --> 16:21.193
You should stay until the storm passes.

16:21.195 --> 16:23.195
We have food, hot water.

16:23.197 --> 16:26.782
Our provisions are meager,
but they're yours to share.

16:26.834 --> 16:28.333
Thank you.

16:28.369 --> 16:30.919
We will tell the king of your kindness.

16:30.954 --> 16:32.421
Good.

16:32.456 --> 16:33.672
Please, this way.

16:38.879 --> 16:40.712
(wind whistling)

16:42.933 --> 16:44.716
(door opening)

16:46.270 --> 16:48.053
♪♪

16:58.565 --> 16:59.564
(splashing)

17:02.453 --> 17:05.237
A royal bath must be something.

17:05.289 --> 17:06.738
Rose petals in the water.

17:09.209 --> 17:11.742
Servant girls massaging your back.

17:11.744 --> 17:14.079
Another princess joke.

17:14.131 --> 17:15.414
What's my line?

17:15.415 --> 17:17.799
I didn't know Rovers bathed at all?

17:17.835 --> 17:19.134
Something like that?

17:21.472 --> 17:24.089
Well, at least we don't lie to ourselves.

17:24.141 --> 17:26.258
We see something we want
and we go after it.

17:27.394 --> 17:29.094
So it's Rover custom to jump into bed

17:29.096 --> 17:31.730
with every guy you meet?

17:31.765 --> 17:34.182
Honestly?

17:34.234 --> 17:35.600
It's not just guys.

17:44.828 --> 17:46.194
What?

17:46.246 --> 17:48.280
Afraid you'll like it?

17:50.033 --> 17:51.450
(scoffing)

17:51.502 --> 17:54.453
You and Cephalo deserve each other.

18:03.297 --> 18:04.796
That mark, what does it mean?

18:07.468 --> 18:09.601
I don't know, I've always had it.

18:16.944 --> 18:18.477
I guess it's just how my first owner

18:18.479 --> 18:20.645
kept track of his property.

18:25.152 --> 18:27.652
- (distant ruffling)
- (gasping)

18:27.654 --> 18:28.904
(clattering)

18:28.956 --> 18:30.489
What was that?

18:30.541 --> 18:32.290
Nothing good.

18:36.163 --> 18:37.579
We Rovers have a saying.

18:37.631 --> 18:40.081
"Golden offers are iron at their core."

18:40.134 --> 18:41.416
I don't trust this Remo guy.

18:41.468 --> 18:42.834
And I don't trust you.

18:42.886 --> 18:43.835
Your point?

18:43.887 --> 18:45.170
That I know my own kind.

18:45.222 --> 18:46.304
And that pointy-eared son of a bitch

18:46.340 --> 18:49.174
is lying about the avalanche.

18:49.226 --> 18:51.009
You know, if we found this place,

18:51.061 --> 18:52.894
so can the Demons.

18:52.930 --> 18:54.095
Maybe we should worry about that

18:54.148 --> 18:56.898
and not some Elvin janitor.

18:56.934 --> 18:57.933
This fortress is impenetrable.

18:57.985 --> 18:59.100
Is it?

18:59.153 --> 19:00.735
We walked right in the front door.

19:00.771 --> 19:02.938
I'd feel better if one of us kept watch.

19:02.990 --> 19:04.406
No one's stopping you, kid.

19:04.441 --> 19:07.192
Pardon the intrusion,
but dinner is served.

19:08.445 --> 19:10.912
Remo, you beautiful bastard.

19:12.533 --> 19:15.867
I'm so hungry I could
eat a Troll's left nut.

19:17.287 --> 19:19.037
(Wil) Sure, I'll take first watch.

19:19.089 --> 19:20.672
I don't need dinner or anything.

19:24.127 --> 19:26.595
♪♪

19:27.931 --> 19:30.015
(sniffing) Smells like death.

19:32.853 --> 19:35.220
Look at all these engravings.

19:35.222 --> 19:36.555
(Arion) This must be the place.

19:38.192 --> 19:40.308
The Druid's book showed a symbol.

19:40.360 --> 19:41.526
We need to locate it.

19:41.562 --> 19:43.728
It's got to be some kind of key.

19:48.318 --> 19:50.569
They all look the same.

20:01.465 --> 20:04.332
This is it, this is the one I saw.

20:04.384 --> 20:05.750
Find me one that matches that.

20:07.254 --> 20:09.254
That's how we find the weapon.

20:19.316 --> 20:20.599
There's one here.

20:24.071 --> 20:25.604
Put your hand on it.

20:25.656 --> 20:27.939
The Codex says we need to
touch it at the same time.

20:38.752 --> 20:41.620
(hissing)

20:45.792 --> 20:48.293
(deep creaking)

21:10.867 --> 21:12.817
♪♪

21:31.088 --> 21:32.837
Thank you.

21:45.652 --> 21:47.936
Don't mind if we trade, do you?

21:47.988 --> 21:48.987
Mine had too many peas in it.

21:49.022 --> 21:49.988
I hate peas.

21:50.023 --> 21:51.272
(chuckling)

21:51.325 --> 21:52.991
Not at all.

22:05.622 --> 22:07.422
I've missed Elvin cooking.

22:07.457 --> 22:09.674
It's an old family recipe.

22:09.710 --> 22:11.459
Where are they, your family?

22:11.511 --> 22:13.511
After the fort was decommissioned,

22:13.547 --> 22:15.680
my wife and I stayed on to keep watch

22:15.716 --> 22:17.716
over the surrounding Troll settlements.

22:17.768 --> 22:20.352
She passed away a few years back.

22:20.387 --> 22:21.803
I'm sorry.

22:21.855 --> 22:23.605
What about the men and
women you tortured here?

22:23.640 --> 22:24.973
Are you sorry about them?

22:25.025 --> 22:26.191
Watch your tongue, Rover.

22:26.226 --> 22:27.809
It's okay.

22:27.861 --> 22:30.562
I know the terrible rumors
people whisper about this place.

22:30.564 --> 22:32.113
We even spread a few ourselves,

22:32.149 --> 22:33.815
hoping to intimidate our enemies.

22:33.867 --> 22:34.983
(chuckling)

22:35.035 --> 22:37.902
But Pykon was a military
outpost, nothing more.

22:37.954 --> 22:40.488
My parents might disagree, if
I could dig their bodies up

22:40.540 --> 22:42.490
from beneath your floor and ask them.

22:42.542 --> 22:45.210
I know you hate Elves, but we
don't murder prisoners of war.

22:48.915 --> 22:50.415
If your parents were prisoners
here, we would have

22:50.467 --> 22:51.583
released them when the war ended.

22:51.585 --> 22:54.085
Perhaps they chose to start a new life,

22:54.087 --> 22:56.137
free of their burdens.

23:07.317 --> 23:10.935
Your ear... it's like mine.

23:13.407 --> 23:15.073
Was your mother human?

23:15.108 --> 23:17.242
My mother's dead.

23:17.277 --> 23:20.111
Sorry to hear that.

23:20.113 --> 23:22.113
So is mine.

23:25.952 --> 23:27.919
So pretty.

23:27.954 --> 23:29.954
What is that?

23:29.956 --> 23:31.456
A seashell.

23:34.761 --> 23:36.461
It belonged to my mom.

23:38.965 --> 23:41.633
Said it reminded her of
where she came from.

23:48.058 --> 23:49.941
Have you ever seen the ocean?

23:52.813 --> 23:56.564
It's like the biggest bath you ever saw.

23:56.616 --> 23:58.149
Blue and sparkly.

23:59.736 --> 24:01.820
I can stare at it for hours,

24:01.822 --> 24:03.655
wondering what's on the other side.

24:09.579 --> 24:12.046
Have you ever been outside?

24:17.838 --> 24:19.721
For keeps?

24:36.523 --> 24:37.989
(grunting)

24:40.076 --> 24:42.360
Mag?

24:42.412 --> 24:45.196
What...

24:45.248 --> 24:46.748
what did you do?

24:53.206 --> 24:56.291
It can be difficult, passing
the time in a place like this,

24:56.343 --> 24:57.959
just the two of us.

24:58.011 --> 25:00.879
There isn't much in the
way of entertainment.

25:00.931 --> 25:03.848
That's why we're so
excited to have guests.

25:09.920 --> 25:11.336
(wind whistling)

25:27.653 --> 25:29.069
Where am I?

25:29.121 --> 25:31.424
Shh, it's not safe.

25:31.535 --> 25:32.901
If he hears you...

25:32.903 --> 25:34.202
(whispering) You're right.

25:34.237 --> 25:34.854
It's not safe.

25:34.929 --> 25:37.430
I need to go, and you
need to come with me.

25:39.601 --> 25:42.568
I can take you somewhere safe,

25:42.604 --> 25:46.272
somewhere you can play with other kids.

25:46.324 --> 25:49.609
Somewhere you can see
the sun and the ocean.

25:50.912 --> 25:52.245
Are there seashells there?

25:52.280 --> 25:53.913
More than you can count.

25:53.948 --> 25:55.831
(screaming in the distance)

25:59.621 --> 26:01.671
(Remo) Come on... stop struggling!

26:05.510 --> 26:06.459
No!

26:08.963 --> 26:10.846
- (grunting)
- (screaming)

26:12.133 --> 26:14.100
(groaning)

26:17.138 --> 26:19.021
(Mag) I told you to be quiet.

26:20.775 --> 26:22.525
(creaking)

26:33.321 --> 26:35.621
(gasping)

26:35.657 --> 26:37.657
(door slamming shut)

26:41.245 --> 26:43.496
Ah, good, you're awake.

26:43.767 --> 26:45.767
I was worried I'd given
you too strong a dose.

26:48.104 --> 26:52.190
A little Wolf's nettle to bring on a nap.

26:52.242 --> 26:55.410
- Of course...
- (grunting)

26:55.445 --> 26:57.745
...if you eat enough of it, like I do,

26:57.781 --> 27:00.582
your body builds up quite a tolerance.

27:00.617 --> 27:02.116
Your turn, Captain.

27:03.203 --> 27:05.286
- Wait!
- (Crispin) Don't tell him anything.

27:05.338 --> 27:07.121
My name is Amberle Elessedil.

27:07.123 --> 27:08.706
Granddaughter of your lord and king,

27:08.758 --> 27:11.960
and by his command I
order you to release us!

27:11.962 --> 27:13.344
Bad idea.

27:16.466 --> 27:21.302
♪♪

27:21.304 --> 27:24.272
A princess?

27:24.307 --> 27:25.857
That changes everything.

27:27.477 --> 27:28.810
(screaming)

27:28.812 --> 27:30.311
(Crispin) You bastard!

27:31.982 --> 27:36.451
My intention was to use the
boy's gift to reach Amberle.

27:36.486 --> 27:37.902
I thought he could help.

27:37.954 --> 27:41.990
What I saw was a man overcome by evil.

27:42.042 --> 27:45.410
You are not capable of
understanding what you saw!

27:45.462 --> 27:47.829
You're not yourself, Allanon.

27:51.167 --> 27:55.503
The Dagda Mor used the boy
to get inside my mind!

27:55.555 --> 27:56.721
The Dagda Mor.

27:56.756 --> 27:59.007
Of course.

27:59.059 --> 28:01.759
The evil everybody fears,
but only you can see.

28:01.811 --> 28:04.512
Tell me, Druid, do you
often commune with Demons?

28:13.189 --> 28:15.023
(shuddering)

28:20.030 --> 28:22.530
What is the meaning of this?

28:22.532 --> 28:25.700
Why conceal a weapon that has
the power to protect us?

28:25.752 --> 28:27.535
To protect you?

28:27.587 --> 28:30.288
That sword is not a salvation,

28:30.340 --> 28:32.340
it is a talisman of evil.

28:32.375 --> 28:35.593
A darkness that is a danger to us all.

28:35.628 --> 28:38.212
It is you who are the danger, Druid.

28:44.688 --> 28:45.803
(grunting)

28:45.855 --> 28:47.221
It was my mistake.

28:47.223 --> 28:49.357
I should have killed you
the first time, Demon.

28:49.392 --> 28:51.526
(groaning)

28:54.898 --> 28:56.864
(thudding)

28:59.736 --> 29:01.536
Finish him.

29:01.571 --> 29:04.038
(raspy breathing)

29:10.413 --> 29:12.130
(groaning)

29:23.593 --> 29:24.475
Where did he go?

29:26.262 --> 29:27.428
What happened?

29:32.936 --> 29:34.852
You did it, my son.

29:34.904 --> 29:37.105
The Druid is no more.

29:42.445 --> 29:44.445
(Amberle whimpering)

29:46.449 --> 29:49.083
Why are you doing this?

29:50.920 --> 29:52.420
(Remo) Because I was trained to.

29:54.791 --> 29:58.042
I don't understand.

29:58.094 --> 29:59.427
Please help me understand.

30:02.048 --> 30:05.883
Many years ago, your grandfather,

30:05.935 --> 30:08.853
the noble and wise King Eventine,

30:08.888 --> 30:11.389
tasked me with the job
of lead interrogator.

30:11.441 --> 30:13.608
It was my solemn duty
to extract information

30:13.643 --> 30:14.642
from our enemies.

30:16.479 --> 30:18.646
But I am not your enemy.

30:18.648 --> 30:20.898
Oh, but you are.

30:20.950 --> 30:22.450
You all are.

30:25.538 --> 30:27.955
And after the war was over,

30:27.991 --> 30:30.792
Eventine sent men here to find me.

30:30.827 --> 30:32.743
- (screws squeaking)
- (gasping)

30:32.796 --> 30:34.495
Imagine my surprise when they told me

30:34.497 --> 30:36.998
Pykon didn't exist.

30:37.050 --> 30:40.001
Then they murdered my wife
and attempted to kill me.

30:42.055 --> 30:44.722
I don't believe you.

30:44.757 --> 30:46.641
My grandfather is an honorable man.

30:46.676 --> 30:48.226
- He wouldn't...
- It doesn't matter what you believe.

30:50.814 --> 30:52.563
I know the truth.

30:54.017 --> 30:56.184
(whimpering)

31:02.325 --> 31:04.242
Please.

31:04.277 --> 31:06.194
I'm on a mission to save the Ellcrys.

31:07.363 --> 31:10.364
If I die, the entire world
will fall into darkness.

31:16.206 --> 31:18.539
I've lived in the
darkness for many years.

31:18.591 --> 31:20.374
(chuckling)

31:20.426 --> 31:22.376
Darkness is my home.

31:22.428 --> 31:23.594
(whimpering)

31:23.630 --> 31:25.379
♪♪

31:25.431 --> 31:26.380
No!

31:26.382 --> 31:28.850
No, no, no, no, no!

31:28.885 --> 31:30.718
(screaming)

31:34.607 --> 31:36.224
(crying) No, please, no!

31:38.561 --> 31:39.527
The Halfling?

31:39.562 --> 31:40.611
He tried to leave.

31:40.647 --> 31:42.280
Wil!

31:43.616 --> 31:45.900
No!

31:45.952 --> 31:47.535
No!

31:47.570 --> 31:49.287
No, no...

31:50.740 --> 31:52.290
Good girl.

31:53.660 --> 31:55.409
No, please...

31:58.324 --> 32:00.190
(wind whistling)

32:00.241 --> 32:01.440
(straining)

32:07.782 --> 32:09.282
Come on, kid.

32:09.284 --> 32:10.783
That's it.

32:12.170 --> 32:13.653
(metal clanking)

32:19.460 --> 32:21.177
For the forebrain.

32:21.212 --> 32:24.463
I stick it through the
nostril and tap it in

32:24.515 --> 32:27.266
ever so gently with this.

32:27.302 --> 32:28.634
(tapping)

32:28.686 --> 32:31.520
(chuckling)

32:31.556 --> 32:34.774
You can bear me a child, live as my wife.

32:34.809 --> 32:36.609
Just like Mag's mother.

32:36.644 --> 32:37.893
She was scared, too.

32:37.945 --> 32:40.813
But after a few taps, no more tears.

32:42.650 --> 32:45.034
But your body will be
perfectly functional.

32:45.069 --> 32:46.068
No...

32:46.120 --> 32:47.320
(whimpering)

32:47.372 --> 32:48.487
Leave her alone!

32:48.489 --> 32:50.156
♪♪

32:50.208 --> 32:51.490
Wil.

32:52.994 --> 32:54.660
(grunting)

32:58.082 --> 33:00.549
♪♪

33:00.585 --> 33:02.251
I'll leave you one eye so you can watch

33:02.303 --> 33:03.836
while I ravish her!

33:05.173 --> 33:07.006
(thudding)

33:09.761 --> 33:13.679
(gurgling)

33:17.101 --> 33:18.351
Thank you.

33:28.112 --> 33:30.112
(panting)

33:30.164 --> 33:31.947
(crying)

33:31.999 --> 33:34.750
I thought I'd lost you.

33:46.881 --> 33:48.347
Hate to break up the honeymoon,

33:48.383 --> 33:50.383
but I'd really like to get
the hell out of here.

33:53.020 --> 33:55.938
You're safe now, but we need to go.

33:56.339 --> 33:57.472
You know a way out of here?

33:58.692 --> 34:00.525
All right, this way.

34:01.828 --> 34:05.697
♪♪

34:05.699 --> 34:07.532
This is madness.

34:07.534 --> 34:08.498
We're lost.

34:08.534 --> 34:10.835
How could I have been so stupid?

34:10.870 --> 34:13.087
I can't believe I trusted a Gnome.

34:13.123 --> 34:14.371
I thought I could

34:14.373 --> 34:16.373
redeem myself for failing
to protect Aine.

34:18.378 --> 34:20.178
Instead, his killer is galloping across

34:20.213 --> 34:21.763
the Four Lands to freedom.

34:21.797 --> 34:23.214
We all failed him.

34:28.471 --> 34:31.022
Everything changed that night.

34:31.056 --> 34:33.775
Yes, it did.

34:33.810 --> 34:37.145
The Ander I loved disappeared,

34:37.197 --> 34:40.231
lost in booze and anger and doubt.

34:41.735 --> 34:44.786
But I wake every morning
hoping he'll return.

34:48.123 --> 34:50.491
(horse whinnying)

34:50.543 --> 34:51.743
Slanter.

34:56.750 --> 34:58.416
You were right.

34:58.418 --> 35:00.885
I didn't believe until I
saw it with my own eyes.

35:03.723 --> 35:05.890
(screaming in the distance)

35:12.398 --> 35:16.267
♪♪

35:18.938 --> 35:20.855
We're doomed.

35:20.907 --> 35:24.492
(screaming continues)

35:38.189 --> 35:39.855
You'll have to go on foot from here.

35:39.915 --> 35:41.114
You're letting me go?

35:41.166 --> 35:43.366
People deserve to know what's coming.

35:43.418 --> 35:45.868
Now go, before I change my mind.

35:51.710 --> 35:56.012
What chance do the Elves have
against a force that size?

35:56.047 --> 35:57.847
I don't know.

35:57.882 --> 36:00.350
But for the sake of all the
races, we must face it.

36:00.385 --> 36:02.101
And you would do so alone?

36:02.137 --> 36:04.103
Perhaps it's what we deserve.

36:06.441 --> 36:09.025
When I tell my tribe what happened to me,

36:09.060 --> 36:11.444
I will speak of your honor.

36:11.479 --> 36:13.563
In another life, we are not enemies.

36:14.950 --> 36:16.616
In another life.

36:25.493 --> 36:27.410
Behind there.

36:31.967 --> 36:33.049
A siege exit.

36:33.084 --> 36:34.917
This must lead to the pass.

36:37.889 --> 36:38.888
(thwacking)

36:38.923 --> 36:39.922
(gasping)

36:41.977 --> 36:44.093
(Remo) I have a rule here at Pykon.

36:44.095 --> 36:45.595
No one leaves.

36:45.597 --> 36:46.929
Mag, come here.

36:48.266 --> 36:49.732
It's over.

36:49.768 --> 36:51.184
She's coming with us.

36:51.236 --> 36:52.986
They're taking me to a new home.

36:53.021 --> 36:54.270
This is your home!

36:54.272 --> 36:55.438
You did this.

36:55.440 --> 36:56.823
You poisoned her with your lies!

36:56.858 --> 36:59.359
Made her into a deceitful
mongrel, like you!

36:59.411 --> 37:00.827
(Mag) Don't!

37:00.862 --> 37:02.328
(gasping) No!

37:02.364 --> 37:03.579
Mag...

37:05.750 --> 37:07.000
- (Amberle) You bastard!
- (groaning)

37:11.122 --> 37:12.121
(clattering)

37:15.960 --> 37:17.260
(gasping)

37:23.184 --> 37:24.767
She's dead.

37:27.222 --> 37:28.971
I'm sorry.

37:30.475 --> 37:32.108
Come on.

37:32.143 --> 37:33.693
Help me open this door.

37:39.651 --> 37:41.701
(Cephalo) Turn it.

37:41.736 --> 37:43.036
(Crispin) Together. Come on.

37:43.071 --> 37:44.404
One... two.

37:44.456 --> 37:45.988
(grunting)

37:51.379 --> 37:53.162
(squeaking)

37:54.549 --> 37:56.165
Come on, we have to go.

38:02.507 --> 38:05.675
(wind whistling)

38:10.765 --> 38:12.181
Is that the Wilderun?

38:12.233 --> 38:13.649
Damn straight!

38:13.685 --> 38:15.184
(guttural roaring)

38:16.688 --> 38:18.271
You've got to be kidding me!

38:18.323 --> 38:20.156
We blew that thing up!

38:20.191 --> 38:22.442
- Come on!
- Get Amberle out of here, now!

38:22.494 --> 38:24.077
We're not leaving you.

38:24.112 --> 38:25.862
I'll be right behind you.

38:25.914 --> 38:27.246
Go!

38:30.168 --> 38:31.367
(growling)

38:35.790 --> 38:38.591
♪♪

38:38.626 --> 38:42.545
(wind whistling)

38:42.597 --> 38:46.933
♪♪

38:58.146 --> 38:59.195
Come on!

38:59.230 --> 39:01.147
What about the others?

39:01.199 --> 39:02.064
We'll send it back

39:02.066 --> 39:05.902
once we're on the other side.

39:05.954 --> 39:07.036
Ready?

39:09.574 --> 39:11.124
Let's go!

39:14.329 --> 39:15.962
(growling)

39:20.418 --> 39:22.084
Crispin?

39:23.922 --> 39:25.138
(growling)

39:25.173 --> 39:26.589
Run!

39:26.591 --> 39:28.391
(growling)

39:34.599 --> 39:36.265
What are you doing?

39:36.267 --> 39:37.650
Saving our asses.

39:40.405 --> 39:41.821
(grunting)

39:41.856 --> 39:43.523
You said we'd help them across!

39:43.575 --> 39:45.191
And bring a Demon with them?

39:45.243 --> 39:46.442
The hell with that!

39:46.494 --> 39:48.494
Eretria!

39:48.530 --> 39:49.779
Help us!

39:51.616 --> 39:54.333
(whacking)

39:54.369 --> 39:56.169
Eretria...

39:56.204 --> 39:59.589
He'll never choose you.

39:59.624 --> 40:00.957
So be it.

40:11.636 --> 40:13.719
She made it, let's go!

40:13.771 --> 40:16.222
Come on. Come on!

40:16.274 --> 40:17.306
(growling)

40:17.358 --> 40:18.441
That thing's right behind us.

40:18.476 --> 40:20.142
Push off and don't look back!

40:25.116 --> 40:26.315
Don't stop!

40:30.205 --> 40:31.621
Sorry, kiddo.

40:31.656 --> 40:33.573
You deserved better.

40:33.625 --> 40:36.125
Just... die already!

40:43.635 --> 40:45.334
(roaring)

